  "prompt": "How much does getting a patent cost?",
  "response": "The cost of obtaining a patent can vary widely depending on several factors:\n\n1. Patent Type:\n- Provisional Patent: $70 - $300\n- Utility Patent: $5,000 - $15,000\n- Design Patent: $1,500 - $3,500\n\n2. Complexity of the invention:\n- Simple inventions cost less\n- Complex technologies cost more\n\n3. Professional fees:\n- Patent attorney/agent fees: $200 - $400 per hour\n- Patent search: $500 - $1,500\n- Drafting application: $5,000 - $10,000\n\n4. Additional costs:\n- USPTO filing fees\n- Maintenance fees\n- Potential legal costs for defending the patent\n\n5. Ongoing expenses:\n- Maintenance fees throughout patent lifetime\n- Renewal fees\n\nTotal costs can range from around $5,000 to $20,000 or more, depending on the specific circumstances. For a precise estimate, it's recommended to consult a patent attorney who can assess your specific invention and needs.",
